Mail-in-a-Box patch: frontend - empty states + search tips click-toggle
=======================================================================

Companion frontend patch improving zero-state UX in three components and
fixing an undiscoverable search tips interaction.

Previously all three empty states showed bare plain text with no visual
treatment, making the UI feel unfinished. The search tips button used a
hold-to-show gesture (mousedown/mouseup) that was completely undiscoverable
on desktop and worked differently on touch.

Changes:

  MessageList.tsx: empty folder/tag view gets a large Inbox or Tag icon
    (lucide, strokeWidth 1.25, muted at 40% opacity) above the existing
    text, which is promoted to font-medium for better hierarchy.

  SearchResults.tsx: no-results state gets a SearchX icon above the
    existing "No results found" text, plus a muted hint line:
    "Try different keywords or check spelling".

  ReadingPane.tsx: no-message-selected state gets a Mail icon above
    updated copy: "Select a message from the list".

  SearchBar.tsx: the ? tips button previously used onMouseDown/onMouseUp/
    onMouseLeave/onTouchStart (hold gesture) to show/hide the tips panel.
    This removes all four handlers and replaces them with a single
    onClick toggle. The mouseHolding useState is also removed. The
    existing outside-click dismiss useEffect and keyboard handlers
    (Enter/Space/Escape) are untouched.

